entries.text: We discussed and went over javaScript OBJECTS and ARRAYS. We covered string interpolation, targeting key values via dot notation and square bracket notation.
The class was introduced to the GRUNT task manager. Initially, it was a bit complicated, however, after a great instructions, it was all so simple.
We're discussing modular workflow of projects. This (to me) is the meat and potatoes of development thus far.
This was an eye-opening challenge, but I enjoyed it.
Soaked up a great bit of knowledge over the last few days.  The class went over array methods.  Understanding the uses of each will greatly improve my skills as a developer.
